<activity xml:id="act-haySuficientes2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>¿Hay suficientes?</title>

<statement>
  <image source="png-source/K.2.B Beta Teacher Guide.AppleTable.png" margins="0% 50%">
    <shortdescription>6 personas en una mesa.</shortdescription>
  </image>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <image source="png-source/K.2 V1 Revisions.FacesChairs.png" margins="0% 50%">
        <shortdescription>5 personas y 4 sillas.</shortdescription>
      </image>
    </li>
    <li>
      <image source="png-source/bowl spoon.png">
        <shortdescription>3 tazones y 7 cucharas.</shortdescription>
      </image>
    </li>
    <li>
      <image source="png-source/K.2 V1 Revisions.ForksPlates.png">
        <shortdescription>10 tenedores y 9 platos.</shortdescription>
      </image>
    </li>
    <li>
      <image source="png-source/K.2 V1 Revisions.StrawsCups.png">
        <shortdescription>6 pajillas y 9 vasos.</shortdescription>
      </image>
    </li>
    </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>Sample responses</p>
  <ol>
    <li>There are not enough chairs for each person. There are more people than chairs.</li>
    <li>There are enough spoons for each bowl. There are fewer bowls than spoons.</li>
    <li>There are enough forks for each plate. There are more forks than plates. </li>
    <li>There are not enough straws for each cup. There are fewer straws than cups.</li>
  </ol>
</solution>


